  "en_notes_yusuf": [
    {
      "note_no": "5113",
      "note": "Here follows a series of eleven aphorisms of ancient wisdom apparently incorporated in current Semitic folklore. The first is that a man's spiritual burden?die responsibility for his sin?must be borne by himself and not by another: Cf. 6:164; 17:15; 35:18; 39:7. There can be no vicarious atonement."
